<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE30631FB1BE8DC7ECB5E83" box="[827,969,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="580">
<typeStatus id="5C098825FFE30631FB1BE8DC7E725E83" box="[827,880,198,219]" pageId="25" pageNumber="580">Type</typeStatus>
species:
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="44B24D04FFE30631FBFAE8DF7E805EA1" authority="Levenstein, 1971 a" authorityName="Levenstein" authorityYear="1971" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Macellicephaloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="25" pageNumber="580" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="berkeleyi">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE30631FBFAE8DF78185E82" box="[986,1306,197,218]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="580">Macellicephaloides berkeleyi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E7234B76FFE30631FD3FE8DF7E805EA1" author="Levenstein RYA" pageId="25" pageNumber="580" pagination="1429 - 1431" refId="ref54553" refString="Levenstein RYA. 1971 a. A new polychaete species of the genus Macellicephaloides from the Aleutian Trench. Journal of the Fisheries Research Board of Canada 28: 1429 - 1431." type="journal article" year="1971">Levenstein, 1971a</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="830D3687FFE30631FB1BE93978535D83" blockId="25.[827,1444,290,987]" pageId="25" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE30631FB1BE93979405F6F" box="[827,1090,290,312]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="580">Diagnosis (emended):</emphasis>
Short body, dorsoventrally flattened, up to 26 segments. Frontal filaments absent. Eyes absent. Median and lateral antennae absent. Facial tubercle absent. Large palpophores. Tentacular segment fused with prostomium, tentaculophores without acicula or chaetae. Pharynx with seven to nine pairs of distal papillae; two pairs of jaws with serrated margin. Dorsal tubercles large (
<taxonomicName id="44B24D04FFE30631FD2EE9E37EC75C75" authorityName="Levenstein" authorityYear="1981" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Bathyedithia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="25" pageNumber="580" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE30631FD2EE9E37EC75C75" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="580">Bathyedithia tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or absent (
<taxonomicName id="44B24D04FFE30631FC7CEA02786E5C75" box="[1116,1388,536,557]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Bathyedithia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="25" pageNumber="580" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="berkeleyi">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE30631FC7CEA02786E5C75" box="[1116,1388,536,557]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="580">Bathyedithia berkeleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="44B24D04FFE30631FB1BEA2C79205C14" authority="Bonifácio &amp; Menot, 2019" authorityName="Bonifácio &amp; Menot" authorityYear="2019" box="[827,1058,566,588]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Bathyedithia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="25" pageNumber="580" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="retierei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE30631FB1BEA2C79205C14" box="[827,1058,566,588]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="580">Bathyedithia retierei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="AAF557EEFFE30631FC09EA2D797C5C14" box="[1065,1150,567,588]" pageId="25" pageNumber="580" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
). Elytrophores prominent, up to ten pairs, on segments 2, 4, 5, 7, 9, 11, 13, 15, 17 and 19. Parapodia subbiramous, notopodia shorter than neuropodia; noto- and neuropodia with elongate acicular lobe; tips of noto- and neuroaciculae not penetrating epidermis. Notochaetae distally with spinous rows; notochaetae more slender than neurochaetae. Neurochaetae numerous, serrated along both margins. From segment 3, ventral cirri inserted medially on neuropodia. Nephridial papillae present (
<taxonomicName id="44B24D04FFE30631FD2FEB507EA25D26" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Bathyedithia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="25" pageNumber="580" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="berkeleyi">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE30631FD2FEB507EA25D26" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="580">Bathyedithia berkeleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="44B24D04FFE30631FBFBEB7379C85D27" authority="Bonifácio &amp; Menot, 2019" authorityName="Bonifácio &amp; Menot" authorityYear="2019" box="[987,1226,873,895]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Bathyedithia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="25" pageNumber="580" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="retierei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE30631FBFBEB7379C85D27" box="[987,1226,873,895]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="580">Bathyedithia retierei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="AAF557EEFFE30631FCF2EB70782A5D27" box="[1234,1320,874,895]" pageId="25" pageNumber="580" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
) or absent (
<taxonomicName id="44B24D04FFE30631FB63EB92795B5DC5" authorityName="Levenstein" authorityYear="1981" box="[835,1113,904,925]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Bathyedithia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="25" pageNumber="580" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE30631FB63EB92795B5DC5" box="[835,1113,904,925]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="580">Bathyedithia tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Pygidium small, with dorsal (
<taxonomicName id="44B24D04FFE30631FB63EBBC79605DE3" authorityName="Levenstein" authorityYear="1981" box="[835,1122,934,955]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Bathyedithia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="25" pageNumber="580" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE30631FB63EBBC79605DE3" box="[835,1122,934,955]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="580">Bathyedithia tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="44B24D04FFE30631FCBBEBBC78985DE3" box="[1179,1434,934,955]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Bathyedithia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="25" pageNumber="580" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="berkeleyi">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE30631FCBBEBBC78985DE3" box="[1179,1434,934,955]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="580">Bathyedithia berkeleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or terminal anus (
<taxonomicName id="44B24D04FFE30631FC25EBDF79E95D83" authority="Bonifácio &amp; Menot, 2019" authorityName="Bonifácio &amp; Menot" authorityYear="2019" box="[1029,1259,965,987]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Bathyedithia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="25" pageNumber="580" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="retierei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE30631FC25EBDF79E95D83" box="[1029,1259,965,987]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="580">Bathyedithia retierei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="AAF557EEFFE30631FCD1EBDC78445D83" box="[1265,1350,966,987]" pageId="25" pageNumber="580" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="830D3687FFE30631FB1BEC1E79835A8A" blockId="25.[827,1443,1028,1234]" pageId="25" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE30631FB1BEC1E7EB35A41" box="[827,945,1028,1049]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="580">Remarks:</emphasis>
The diagnosis of genus 
<taxonomicName id="44B24D04FFE30631FCDEEC1E78A15A41" authorityName="Pettibone" authorityYear="1976" box="[1278,1443,1028,1049]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Bathyedithia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="25" pageNumber="580" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE30631FCDEEC1E78A15A41" box="[1278,1443,1028,1049]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="580">Bathyedithia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is emended to include a character observed in the species described below and the species 
<taxonomicName id="44B24D04FFE30631FD2CEC5B79815A2D" authority="Levenstein, 1981" authorityName="Levenstein" authorityYear="1981" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Bathyedithia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="25" pageNumber="580" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE30631FD2CEC5B7EBC5A2D" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="580">Bathyedithia tuberculata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E7234B76FFE30631FBE2EC7A79815A2D" author="Levenstein RYA" box="[962,1155,1120,1142]" pageId="25" pageNumber="580" pagination="26 - 36" refId="ref54702" refString="Levenstein RYA. 1981. Some peculiarities of the distribution of the family Polynoidae from the Canada basin of the Arctic Ocean. Transactions of the P. P. Shirshov Institute of Oceanology 115: 26 - 36." type="journal article" year="1981">Levenstein, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
: ten pairs of elytrophores; as well as with characters observed in the new species: the presence of a terminal anus and the number of pairs of pharyngeal papillae.
</paragraph>
